spice-vdagent

###  DISPLAY MANAGER — boot to the login screen
accountsservice
###  on-screen keyboard for the SDDM greeter (accessibility — InputMethod=qtvirtualkeyboard)
###  MUST be qt5 — sddm forces DisplayServer=x11 (999-force-x11) so the live greeter is the Qt5 sddm-greeter; qt6-virtualkeyboard is invisible to it and the theme falls back to embedded
qt5-virtualkeyboard
sddm-git

###  DESKTOP / WM EDITIONS — MANAGED BY build-the-iso.sh
###  Commented blocks; the build uncomments the block(s) named in build.conf
###  editions= (e.g. "xfce ohmychadwm i3"). Each block is the session's full set
###  from ATT's desktopr.py; duplicate package lines are harmless (pacman dedupes).
###  XFCE is an edition too now (NO longer force-installed): a build can omit it
###  entirely — e.g. editions="cinnamon" = pure Cinnamon, no XFCE, none in SDDM.
###  Default editions = "xfce ohmychadwm" (build.conf.defaults) → default ISO unchanged.
###  The login session is set from build.conf default_session (see build-the-iso.sh).
